title: 5 Reasons Why You Need To Quit Smoking Weed & Start Vaping It
description:
http://www.whatsyourvapetemp.com/ - What's up VapeTempers! Today, we're going to give you our top 5 reasons on why you should stop smoking weed, and start vaping it! Click now to learn why.

Here's our top 5 reasons why:

Reason #5 - More Efficient
Combustion of Marijuana only releases 25% of active ingredients like THC. Depending on the vaporizer and temperatures, vaporization can release 50% of the active ingredients allowing you to effectively use the same amount of marijuana for 2x longer than combustion. Saving you some hard earned green!

Reason #4 - Smell
Though vaporization isn't completely odorless, it smells far less than combustion. It also passes faster and doesn't soak into clothing and furniture as it does with combustion. 

Reason # 3 - Less Carcinogens
Vaporization produces 95% less carcinogens than combustion which makes for a smoother and better tasting experience. These carcinogens are toxic chemicals and are the leading causes of many lung diseases and cancer. 

Reason # 2 - Buzzcrafting 
That’s right! Buzz crafting. Or the art of crafting your buzz with a vaporizer that has precise controls. Since different active ingredients are release at different temperature ranges, you can craft the high you are looking for to either get the munches, watch tv, or fall asleep.

And Reason # 1 - ABV or Already Been Vaped Marijuana
If you don’t know what ABV is by now you have been vaping wrong. Since your vaped marijuana goes through a decarboxylation process, this essentially activates the THC. Even though vaping your herb is more efficient than smoking it, there is still some active ingredients like THC left inside. This mean you can eat your ABV with just adding a fat source and no heating necessary.


*** WE LIKE BEING SOCIAL ***

title: Beginner Vaping - How To Vape Like A Pro, Using A Vape Pen or Vaporizer - Marijuana, Cannabis, THC
description:
Have you ever wanted to learn how to vape? This quick video demonstrates all of the essentials that you'll need in order to vape like a pro.

People have smoked cannabis for centuries to enjoy its health benefits like reducing stress and stimulating appetite. But smoking releases harsh toxins that damage your lungs and can cause cancer. Plus it’s messy. And stinky.

Vaporizers heat cannabis to temperatures below burning point (451°F) which releases potent vapor with the same physical and mental benefits as smoking marijuana, but without the harsh smoke toxins1. And the herb odor is much less.

How Willy Nelson Vapes: “I’ve changed my habits a little bit. I’ve smoked so much and I got congestion from it, wheezing in the night and coughing. So I switched over to a vaporizer. You don’t get any smoke, and you don’t get any heat. And for a singer, or someone’s lungs, it’s much, much healthier. There’s pot in the vaporizer, but when you puff it in, you’re getting vapors, but not heat and not smoke. I think it’s even stronger, too.”

Four Benefits of Vaporizing
1. It's healthier than smoking — vapor contains virtually none of the harsh toxins found in smoke.
2. Works fast and is easy to control dose, unlike edible pot brownies or bread.
3. Efficient; generally you use 10–30% less herb than smoking pipes, joints or bongs.
4. Hardly any smell, only a faint herb odor that allows you to be more discreet.

title: 3 Pros and 3 Cons of Using Vape Pens to Smoke Marijuan
description:
Every marijuana consumer has his or her preferred way of ingesting cannabis whether is be a joint, pipe, bong, vape, or edible. Vape pens are a portable and popular way to consume marijuana, so much so that some users prefer vape pens over any other method of consumption. This form of ingesting marijuana is becoming more common among users because they look just like pens, so they’re easy to transport and use. Consumers can simply keep their pens in their pockets and vape on the go whenever they please. This simplicity and portability isn’t without a glitch though, because like every other smoking method, vape pens have both pros and cons. 

First, vape pens are a favorite among users because there is no combustion. The flower or oil that is inhaled doesn’t burn, so users don’t inhale any of the toxins associated with smoking. For this reason, vaping is also healthier than smoking, because there’s no risk of inhaling tar or lighter fluid. This lack of chemicals inhaled might also be the reason why vapes pull smoother than smoking. Some vapes also allow users to control the temperature, so they can adjust if it’s too harsh. Even though these vape pens seem very simple to use, they certainly take time for users to adjust to because each battery has different features that make for an interesting high experience.

title: Study: Vaping Weed is the Best Option for Health and THC
description:
A study out of the University of California San Fransisco from May '07 took 18 people and had them either smoke or vape dried cannabis flower 3 times a day for 6 days. 
Read the blog and full study here:
https://hempeagle.com/blogs/news/stud... 

They alternated days. For example on day 1 a participate would smoke weed 3 times a day and on day 2 they would vape weed 3 times a day. Toxic levels and levels of THC were measured during each session and this is what they found:

Participants got all the medicine they needed but without any toxic side effects. Here is an excerpt form the UCSF website: “Using CO as an indicator, there was virtually no exposure to harmful combustion products using the vaporizing device. Since it replicates smoking’s efficiency at producing the desired THC effect using smaller amounts of the active ingredient as opposed to pill forms, this device has great potential for improving the therapeutic utility of THC,” said study co-author Neal L. Benowitz, MD, UCSF professor of medicine, psychiatry and biopharmaceutical sciences. He added that pills tend to provide patients with more THC than they need for optimal therapeutic effect and increase side effects.
After the study, participants said they preferred vaporizing. Patients felt so much better overall when they were vaping weed vs. smoking it! Here is another excerpt from the UCSF website: Patients rated the “high” they experienced from both smoking and vaporization and there was no difference between the two methods by patient self-report of the effect, according to study findings. In addition, patients were asked which method they preferred.“By a significant majority, patients preferred vaporization to smoking, choosing the route of delivery with the fewest side effects and greatest efficiency,” said Benowitz.
We at Hemp Eagle are proponents of vaping dried cannabis and know that it is the best way to medicate. Simply put, when vaping weed you feel the euphoria more and the side effects less. Vaping with the right oven device (vaporizer), like the one used in this study, will make you never want to smoke weed again. The device used in this study is the famous Volcano Vaporizer. Side notes: This study used dried marijuana flower (weed) as the material for the vaporization. No vape oils or concentrates were used in this study. The dried flower is put in a medical grade oven in a device know as a vaporizer. The oven heats the weed to lower temperature which preserves the cannabinoids that are in the plant. When smoking weed, the high heat of the flame will burn off almost all of the healing and soothing cannabinoids in the weed. title: Dealing of THC vape juice linked to murder of 17-year-old Eagle Scout, allegedly
description:
A 17-year-old Eagle Scout who was the son of a prominent Prince George’s County homicide detective was allegedly dealing THC liquid used in vaping, according to court documents.

The documents said Bradley Alan Brown "has recently been selling THC vape cartridges," according to witness accounts.

Brown had been using Snapchat to communicate with suspect Darryl Edward Freeman the afternoon preceding his murder, according to court documents. Brown was found fatally shot Tuesday night in the driveway of his family’s home on Warehouse Landing Road in the Bryan’s Road section of Charles County, Md., police said. 

Freeman is a football player at Thomas Stone High School in Charles County, and witnesses reported he had been selling marijuana, according to the charging papers.

title: EPISODE #44 Cannabis and Vaping Tech with JJ O'Brien, Chief Strategy Officer at PAX Labs
description:
We’re joined this week by JJ O’Brien, Chief Strategy Officer at PAX Labs, a Silicon Valley vape company. PAX Labs originally developed the Juul e-cigarette which is now sold across the world. 

In this episode, we explore North American cannabis markets, the use of vaporisers as a method for cannabis consumption, and the importance of quality and durable design.

Episode Summary

JJ graduated from business school in 2011 and started his career as a consultant in the finance world before entering the cannabis space in 2014. He joined Pax in 2016 as a manager, and has since helped to launch the Pax Era vapouriser into several markets across North America.

JJ suggests that cannabis market growth is extremely hard to predict due to a multitude of factors including constantly changing laws and processes, and conflicting federal and state laws.

In the USA, cannabis markets are localised and governed within states, meaning if you buy cannabis in California it has been grown there. 

Cannabis products are not able to cross state lines, creating hyper-localised markets and issues with scalability.

Pax Labs originally developed the Juul e-cigarette which was spun out of Pax Labs as an independent company in 2017. The products now serve two different markets and exist as independent entities.

PAX Labs was founded with the goal of creating responsible, enjoyable, and personalized vaporizer experiences. Pax Labs are in essence a hardware company who sell consumer technology.

The company's newest product, the Pax 3 is a portable cannabis vaporizer for dry herb and extracts. It features a conduction oven which heats cannabis flower gently, temperature settings which allow the user to choose their own combination of vapour and flavour for consumption. 

There is a clear market in the US and North America for a discreet portable vapouriser.

Pax Labs invest heavily in research and product development, with half of the company being directly involved with the engineering of its products.
